Reasoning: The paper deals with the degrees of freedom of a communication network, specifically the SISO X-channel, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The alternating channel state information at the transmitters (CSIT) is a key aspect of the paper, which could also place it under the networked information (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also involves interference management (cs.SI) and channel coding (cs.CC) techniques. Finally, the paper could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) applications that require efficient communication networks.
